So, what's next?

1034
01:02:54,773 --> 01:02:57,492
We need to talk to your assistant,
Mrs. Black.

1035
01:02:57,653 --> 01:02:58,642
Call her.

1036
01:02:58,973 --> 01:03:01,612
You feel confident she'll back you
on the time?

1037
01:03:03,133 --> 01:03:05,044
Melissa, yeah, yeah.

1038
01:03:05,213 --> 01:03:07,727
She's okay. She's a straight arrow.

1039
01:03:09,973 --> 01:03:12,043
We're going to talk to her...

1040
01:03:13,133 --> 01:03:16,125
...and you're not going
to talk to anybody, all right?

1041
01:03:17,333 --> 01:03:18,368
All right?

1042
01:03:21,653 --> 01:03:22,802
No comment.

1043
01:03:26,013 --> 01:03:27,241
There they are!

1044
01:03:29,453 --> 01:03:31,284
Kevin, how about a couple shots?

1045
01:03:31,373 --> 01:03:34,171
How does it feel to get
the biggest murder trial in New York?

1046
01:03:34,253 --> 01:03:37,643
Look over here! Are you really
going to plead Cullen not guilty?

1047
01:03:37,733 --> 01:03:39,086
What is happening?

1048
01:03:39,173 --> 01:03:42,085
Since the case,
Kevin's picture's been in the paper.

1049
01:03:42,533 --> 01:03:45,366
He always did like to stick his nose
in the camera.

1050
01:03:46,453 --> 01:03:48,364
- Sorry about that.
- No problem.

1051
01:03:48,533 --> 01:03:50,330
Did you have a nice dinner?

1052
01:03:50,453 --> 01:03:52,648
Oh, I surely did. Are you hungry?

1053
01:03:52,733 --> 01:03:54,405
Oh, no, ma'am. Thank you.

1054
01:03:55,293 --> 01:03:56,806
Welcome to Babylon, Ma.

1055
01:03:56,893 --> 01:03:58,326
Speak of the devil.

1056
01:04:00,373 --> 01:04:02,967
I was just telling them the Moyez story.

1057
01:04:03,613 --> 01:04:04,762
Really?

1058
01:04:05,853 --> 01:04:07,002
This is your mother.

1059
01:04:07,093 --> 01:04:08,606
Yes, Mom, this is...

1060
01:04:08,773 --> 01:04:09,922
John Milton.

1061
01:04:11,413 --> 01:04:12,641
Alice Lomax.

1062
01:04:13,053 --> 01:04:15,169
It's a pleasure to meet you.

1063
01:04:16,013 --> 01:04:17,366
How do you do?

1064
01:04:19,973 --> 01:04:21,929
- You're looking lovely.
- Thanks.

1065
01:04:24,853 --> 01:04:26,571
I believe you met Christabella.

1066
01:04:26,653 --> 01:04:28,086
Yes, I think we did.

1067
01:04:28,213 --> 01:04:29,692
And Gizelle.

1068
01:04:29,853 --> 01:04:31,764
Fresh in from Paris.

1069
01:04:31,853 --> 01:04:33,650
Great.

1070
01:04:34,493 --> 01:04:35,812
Nice to meet you.

1071
01:04:38,013 --> 01:04:39,446
Three for you...

1072
01:04:39,613 --> 01:04:40,966
...and my place.

1073
01:04:41,053 --> 01:04:42,247
Thanks for the champagne.

1074
01:04:42,333 --> 01:04:44,403
You're very welcome, Kevin.

1075
01:04:45,973 --> 01:04:49,966
This isn't really your first visit
to New York, now, is it, Mrs. Lomax?

1076
01:04:53,373 --> 01:04:54,203
Yes.

1077
01:05:01,333 --> 01:05:04,962
You've done one hell of a job
bringing him up, Mrs. Lomax.

1078
01:05:05,853 --> 01:05:06,888
I'm sure...

1079
01:05:06,973 --> 01:05:08,565
...it wasn't easy.

1080
01:05:11,093 --> 01:05:12,242
No.

1081
01:05:15,253 --> 01:05:16,766
Mom, we're here.

1082
01:05:17,173 --> 01:05:18,526
Good night to you.

1083
01:05:19,573 --> 01:05:21,643
Good night, Mary Ann.

1084
01:05:22,133 --> 01:05:23,612
Kevin, hang on.

1085
01:05:25,453 --> 01:05:27,250
How about Cullen? How's it going?

1086
01:05:27,333 --> 01:05:28,732
Everything on beam?

1087
01:05:28,973 --> 01:05:30,770
That's a long conversation.

1088
01:05:31,493 --> 01:05:33,290
Want to come up and tell me?

1089
01:05:33,533 --> 01:05:34,648
Now?

1090
01:05:42,133 --> 01:05:43,566
Let's talk tomorrow.

1091
01:05:46,293 --> 01:05:47,328
You sure?

1092
01:05:56,813 --> 01:05:59,691
Is that what you're doing
when you're working late?

1093
01:05:59,933 --> 01:06:01,252
What're you talking about?

1094
01:06:01,333 --> 01:06:03,528
You know exactly what I'm talking about.

1095
01:06:03,613 --> 01:06:05,604
- That's ridiculous.
- Yeah, right.

1096
01:06:05,853 --> 01:06:07,047
I'm going to bed.

1097
01:06:07,133 --> 01:06:08,964
- Good night, Alice.
- 'Night.

1098
01:06:22,013 --> 01:06:23,765
Oh, shit!

1099
01:06:27,733 --> 01:06:29,086
Mom, what are you doing?

1100
01:06:29,173 --> 01:06:30,606
I'm going home.

1101
01:06:30,773 --> 01:06:32,445
What are you talking about?

1102
01:06:32,533 --> 01:06:34,603
I don't feel right.

1103
01:06:34,773 --> 01:06:37,003
Look, you just got here.

1104
01:06:37,813 --> 01:06:41,488
And I just got my teeth kicked in
on the front page, so I gotta run.

1105
01:06:42,453 --> 01:06:44,125
We'll talk later, okay?

1106
01:06:49,173 --> 01:06:51,004
I have to go, Kevin.

1107
01:06:51,573 --> 01:06:52,926
I miss my church.

1108
01:06:53,173 --> 01:06:57,212
This is New York. There must be
20,000 churches. Take your pick.

1109
01:06:58,293 --> 01:07:00,409
You need to do a better job with Mary Ann.

1110
01:07:00,493 --> 01:07:02,051
She is not well.

1111
01:07:02,133 --> 01:07:04,852
- This place is not good for her.
- So stay.

1112
01:07:05,013 --> 01:07:07,163
Take care of her, if you're so concerned.

1113
01:07:07,253 --> 01:07:08,572
Help me out.

1114
01:07:09,013 --> 01:07:11,049
I'll take her home if you let me.

1115
01:07:11,493 --> 01:07:13,643
This is home. Understand?

1116
01:07:13,813 --> 01:07:15,087
This is where we live.

1117
01:07:15,173 --> 01:07:17,243
I'm not going back to Gainesville.

1118
01:07:17,333 --> 01:07:18,925
Unbelievable.

1119
01:07:19,813 --> 01:07:20,962
"Wide is the gate...

1120
01:07:21,053 --> 01:07:23,965
"...and broad is the way
that leadeth to temptation."

1121
01:07:24,293 --> 01:07:25,806
It's a little early for Scripture.

1122
01:07:25,893 --> 01:07:28,612
I'm going to work.
You can do whatever you want.

1123
01:07:51,333 --> 01:07:53,244
Does my babysitter have to testify?

1124
01:07:53,333 --> 01:07:56,370
We need her to establish
the time you returned home.

1125
01:07:56,853 --> 01:07:59,413
She doesn't have a green card,
is why I ask.

1126
01:07:59,893 --> 01:08:02,009
I would hate for her to get in trouble.

1127
01:08:02,093 --> 01:08:03,128
Tell you what, Melissa...

1128
01:08:03,213 --> 01:08:06,603
Let's talk to her first. See where
she stands and take it from there.

1129
01:08:06,693 --> 01:08:09,253
I'll make sure Melissa gets down to the car.

1130
01:08:09,333 --> 01:08:11,563
Mr. Cullen didn't kill those people.

1131
01:08:11,733 --> 01:08:14,691
I know him. He's a difficult man,
but he couldn't kill anyone.

1132
01:08:14,773 --> 01:08:16,968
That's why we're all working so hard.

1133
01:08:17,893 --> 01:08:18,928
Thank you.

1134
01:08:20,373 --> 01:08:22,841
Can I have the car stop
at my ex-husband's?

1135
01:08:23,253 --> 01:08:25,403
- My son left his jacket there.
- Sure.

1136
01:08:29,493 --> 01:08:34,044
Remember, no shredding in the building
trash, only in the private refuse.

1137
01:08:34,213 --> 01:08:37,171
Excelsior Securities, who's handling that?

1138
01:08:37,333 --> 01:08:39,403
- I am.
- All this has got to go.

1139
01:08:39,733 --> 01:08:41,803
Guatemala, Sudan, Cyprus...

1140
01:08:43,813 --> 01:08:47,249
Vagada Holdings, it'll take you all night.
Just Vagada Holdings.

1141
01:08:49,173 --> 01:08:51,641
I thought I was the only one working late.

1142
01:08:54,693 --> 01:08:55,728
So did we.

1143
01:08:56,693 --> 01:08:59,332
Back to work. This is not a break.

1144
01:08:59,533 --> 01:09:00,522
Good news.

1145
01:09:00,613 --> 01:09:03,571
We just wrapped up with
Cullen's assistant. Looks like a great alibi.

1146
01:09:03,653 --> 01:09:05,291
What a pleasant surprise.

1147
01:09:08,213 --> 01:09:10,044
Looks like you've got your hands full.

1148
01:09:10,133 --> 01:09:12,203
It's just a little...

1149
01:09:12,413 --> 01:09:13,732
...housekeeping.

1150
01:09:14,453 --> 01:09:16,125
If anyone should ask...

1151
01:09:17,093 --> 01:09:18,606
...you never saw this.

1152
01:09:19,013 --> 01:09:20,207
Who would ask?

1153
01:09:21,373 --> 01:09:22,362
Weaver.

1154
01:09:22,493 --> 01:09:23,608
Who's that?

1155
01:09:24,773 --> 01:09:27,082
Justice Department. Weaver Commission.

1156
01:09:29,493 --> 01:09:30,687
You don't know about him?

1157
01:09:30,773 --> 01:09:31,808
Sorry.

1158
01:09:33,493 --> 01:09:34,528
How nice for you.

1159
01:09:34,613 --> 01:09:39,209
Grab your coat. The night is young.
We're going to the Garden. Ringside.

1160
01:09:39,413 --> 01:09:40,528
Title fight.

1161
01:09:40,613 --> 01:09:42,126
Roy Jones, Jr.

1162
01:09:42,213 --> 01:09:43,931
I have to call Mary Ann.

1163
01:09:44,013 --> 01:09:45,332
Do it on the way.

1164
01:09:47,293 --> 01:09:48,521
Get my message?

1165
01:09:48,773 --> 01:09:51,082
I did. You write beautifully.

1166
01:09:54,773 --> 01:09:56,843
What's this Weaver Commission?

1167
01:09:57,173 --> 01:09:59,050
I don't like to micro-manage.

1168
01:09:59,213 --> 01:10:01,169
Find the talent, then delegate.

1169
01:10:01,733 --> 01:10:04,008
Who the hell knows what Eddie's up to?

1170
01:10:04,453 --> 01:10:07,092
He's got a lot of fingers in a lot of pies.

1171
01:10:07,973 --> 01:10:09,167
Excuse me.

1172
01:10:09,333 --> 01:10:11,403
What the fuck are you looking at?

1173
01:10:12,373 --> 01:10:14,284
You. You deaf or something?
You don't hear me?

1174
01:10:14,373 --> 01:10:15,965
I hear you fine.

1175
01:10:16,133 --> 01:10:17,805
So get the fuck out of my car.

1176
01:10:17,893 --> 01:10:21,932
Why? I didn't know it was your car.
I'm having a good time here.

1177
01:10:22,013 --> 01:10:23,605
I'm telling you, motherfucker...

1178
01:10:23,693 --> 01:10:24,842
...get the fuck out of my car...

1179
01:10:24,933 --> 01:10:25,763
Shit.

1180
01:10:25,893 --> 01:10:28,248
Get out before I cut your throat.

1181
01:10:28,413 --> 01:10:29,448
Fuck that.

1182
01:10:53,693 --> 01:10:55,012
How do you know?

1183
01:10:59,933 --> 01:11:01,082
Enjoy yourself.

1184
01:11:01,173 --> 01:11:02,652
You still got time.

1185
01:11:03,133 --> 01:11:06,091
There's a train coming the other way.
You'll just catch it.

1186
01:11:06,173 --> 01:11:08,084
You'll thank me in the morning.

1187
01:11:08,213 --> 01:11:09,441
If you ain't right...

1188
01:11:09,533 --> 01:11:10,648
I'm right.

1189
01:11:10,813 --> 01:11:11,882
You'll see.

1190
01:11:13,493 --> 01:11:14,812
Invigorating.

1191
01:11:15,733 --> 01:11:17,371
What did you say to him?

1192
01:11:18,453 --> 01:11:22,287
I told him if he didn't leave us alone,
you'd kick his ass.

1193
01:11:22,453 --> 01:11:25,490
Look, there's a lady getting up
from her seat. Come on.

1194
01:11:26,933 --> 01:11:29,652
Give it to him! You want this round?
You are on!

1195
01:11:30,453 --> 01:11:33,331
Roy's gonna get him. Now, now, now!

1196
01:11:43,253 --> 01:11:44,402
Fixed!

1197
01:11:50,133 --> 01:11:52,522
- What a beauty!
- I'm glad you could come!

1198
01:11:53,213 --> 01:11:56,649
I want you to meet my new heavyweight,
here: Kevin Lomax.

1199
01:11:56,813 --> 01:11:58,132
How are you?

1200
01:11:58,293 --> 01:11:59,282
I'm well.

1201
01:12:17,653 --> 01:12:19,086
And say what?

1202
01:12:19,253 --> 01:12:21,209
He's the senior partner at the...

1203
01:12:23,573 --> 01:12:25,848
You're really starting to piss me off.

1204
01:12:34,773 --> 01:12:36,684
Yes, I'm having one cigarette.

1205
01:12:36,853 --> 01:12:40,209
You want me to lie?
One cigarette after seven months is not...

1206
01:12:40,373 --> 01:12:42,329
That's exactly what I'm saying!

1207
01:12:44,093 --> 01:12:45,811
Go to bed. I have no idea.

1208
01:12:56,373 --> 01:12:58,762
Stop. This guy pays our bills.

1209
01:12:58,933 --> 01:13:02,562
The food, the heat, the rent
on that enormous apartment we live in.

1210
01:13:03,733 --> 01:13:05,212
I live there, too.

1211
01:13:09,973 --> 01:13:11,565
Give it back to me!

1212
01:13:17,853 --> 01:13:19,047
Babs Coleman.

1213
01:13:19,413 --> 01:13:20,892
Kevin Lomax.

1214
01:13:20,973 --> 01:13:23,851
Babs is from Georgia Tech.
It's your neck of the woods.

1215
01:13:23,933 --> 01:13:24,922
There's Tiffany.

1216
01:13:25,013 --> 01:13:27,481
New additions. Where are you from?

1217
01:13:27,613 --> 01:13:29,205
Don't tell me!

1218
01:13:30,133 --> 01:13:31,282
Michigan!

1219
01:13:31,773 --> 01:13:34,492
How'd you know? Oh, my goodness.

1220
01:13:34,653 --> 01:13:36,052
How did he know?

1221
01:13:36,213 --> 01:13:37,692
That is so good.

1222
01:13:52,213 --> 01:13:53,487
Cheers.

1223
01:14:43,975 --> 01:14:45,249
Hello?

1224
01:14:46,295 --> 01:14:47,614
Who is there?

1225
01:14:48,375 --> 01:14:49,967
I got a knife.

1226
01:15:11,895 --> 01:15:13,408
Oh, Jesus.

1227
01:15:20,055 --> 01:15:21,408
Baby...

1228
01:15:21,895 --> 01:15:23,772
...how'd you get here?

1229
01:15:25,415 --> 01:15:27,087
Are you okay?

1230
01:15:29,335 --> 01:15:30,609
Oh, God.

1231
01:15:33,735 --> 01:15:35,407
Where's your mommy?

1232
01:15:36,695 --> 01:15:39,812
You ain't got no mommy?
What do you got there?

1233
01:15:40,055 --> 01:15:42,205
What are you playing with?

1234
01:15:43,455 --> 01:15:45,286
What are you playing with?

1235
01:15:51,335 --> 01:15:52,927
Oh, God!

1236
01:16:01,975 --> 01:16:03,567
Baby, please.

1237
01:16:03,855 --> 01:16:05,891
Baby, there is no blood.

1238
01:16:06,615 --> 01:16:08,685
There is no blood. It was a dream.

1239
01:16:08,775 --> 01:16:10,128
It was a dream.

1240
01:16:11,415 --> 01:16:13,724
It's not a dream if it's true.

1241
01:16:15,255 --> 01:16:19,533
Look, let's get you undressed
and in the tub, okay?

1242
01:16:19,735 --> 01:16:20,770
No!

1243
01:16:21,175 --> 01:16:22,688
I know you.

1244
01:16:24,295 --> 01:16:26,365
You'll leave me now for sure.

1245
01:16:27,015 --> 01:16:29,245
No! Get away from me!

1246
01:16:33,055 --> 01:16:34,693
I'm confused.

1247
01:16:35,015 --> 01:16:36,130
Why?

1248
01:16:37,015 --> 01:16:38,368
What is it now?

1249
01:16:40,535 --> 01:16:42,173
Did you like the green?

1250
01:16:42,695 --> 01:16:44,287
You did, didn't you?

1251
01:16:44,455 --> 01:16:45,808
We should go back to the green.

1252
01:16:45,895 --> 01:16:48,614
I'm calling the doctor.
I'm going to get you some help.

1253
01:16:48,695 --> 01:16:50,526
They took my ovaries, Kevin.

1254
01:16:53,655 --> 01:16:55,885
They took my ovaries!

1255
01:16:56,055 --> 01:16:58,046
I told you! Right here!

1256
01:16:58,455 --> 01:17:01,492
Mary Ann, it was a nightmare.
It didn't happen.

1257
01:17:05,175 --> 01:17:08,292
My sisters have
seven children between them.

1258
01:17:11,335 --> 01:17:14,008
My mother had Derek when she was 45.

1259
01:17:14,295 --> 01:17:16,729
You could've set a clock by my periods.

1260
01:17:16,895 --> 01:17:17,884
Baby...

1261
01:17:18,215 --> 01:17:20,649
...what are you talking about?

1262
01:17:22,215 --> 01:17:24,570
Kevin, I can't have children.

1263
01:17:25,015 --> 01:17:25,970
What?

1264
01:17:26,615 --> 01:17:27,764
Says who?

1265
01:17:31,015 --> 01:17:32,528
The doctor.

1266
01:17:33,175 --> 01:17:35,166
I was there yesterday.

1267
01:17:36,375 --> 01:17:39,367
"Non-specific ovarian failure."

1268
01:17:41,335 --> 01:17:42,688
That's ridiculous.

1269
01:17:45,815 --> 01:17:46,850
Oh, God.

1270
01:17:48,535 --> 01:17:50,173
Did you just hear that?

1271
01:17:51,175 --> 01:17:52,210
Listen.

1272
01:17:54,135 --> 01:17:55,488
Can you hear that?

1273
01:17:58,455 --> 01:17:59,410
No.

1274
01:18:03,255 --> 01:18:05,564
You're going to leave me, aren't you?

1275
01:18:09,255 --> 01:18:10,847
I know you.

1276
01:18:11,975 --> 01:18:13,010
God...

1277
01:18:15,655 --> 01:18:17,247
No, Kevin.

1278
01:18:17,655 --> 01:18:19,088
It's these monsters.

1279
01:18:20,135 --> 01:18:22,365
I dreamt about this.

1280
01:18:23,575 --> 01:18:25,008
Baby, I gotta take this.

1281
01:18:25,095 --> 01:18:27,484
No, you've gotta listen to me.

1282
01:18:29,335 --> 01:18:30,688
I gotta take this.

1283
01:18:32,615 --> 01:18:34,128
It's going to be okay.

1284
01:18:41,095 --> 01:18:42,050
Fuck!

1285
01:18:42,215 --> 01:18:44,524
I knew the D.A. Was holding out on us.

1286
01:18:44,695 --> 01:18:47,334
Get the discovery package
over here, right now.

1287
01:18:48,135 --> 01:18:50,205
I don't care. Find Cullen.

1288
01:18:58,935 --> 01:19:01,893
I get one supervised hour a week
with my stepdaughter.

1289
01:19:02,055 --> 01:19:05,252
I am in there with two shrinks
and three social workers.

1290
01:19:05,415 --> 01:19:08,134
You better have a good reason
for calling me out.

1291
01:19:08,215 --> 01:19:11,252
Your wife, the day she was killed,
had lunch with a friend.

1292
01:19:11,335 --> 01:19:14,486
She says, and I quote:
"Alex is fucking around and I can prove it."

1293
01:19:14,575 --> 01:19:16,452
That's hearsay. That never gets in.

1294
01:19:16,535 --> 01:19:17,729
Wrong answer.

