I've had enough of your fucking game!

1537
01:31:12,055 --> 01:31:15,365
Why don't you take your questions
and shove them up your ass!

1538
01:31:32,855 --> 01:31:34,174
What's happening?

1539
01:31:34,295 --> 01:31:36,047
It's Eddie Barzoon.

1540
01:31:36,215 --> 01:31:37,250
What about him?

1541
01:31:37,335 --> 01:31:39,405
He's dead. He was killed.

1542
01:31:39,575 --> 01:31:41,133
- When?
- Last night.

1543
01:31:41,295 --> 01:31:43,604
- In the park.
- He was running, if you can believe it.

1544
01:31:43,695 --> 01:31:45,367
What is wrong with people?

1545
01:31:45,455 --> 01:31:47,810
At least they got the scumbags who did it.

1546
01:31:47,895 --> 01:31:48,805
Who?

1547
01:31:48,975 --> 01:31:50,772
Two old homeless crazies.

1548
01:31:54,615 --> 01:31:56,287
You're due in court in 30 minutes.

1549
01:31:56,375 --> 01:31:59,173
- Get your things together.
- Are we finished in here or what?

1550
01:31:59,255 --> 01:32:02,406
I'll bring Melissa down to the car.
You better get going.

1551
01:32:05,335 --> 01:32:08,645
I want you to put Eddie aside.
Let me worry about it.

1552
01:32:10,255 --> 01:32:12,166
You've got to deal with Cullen.

1553
01:32:12,375 --> 01:32:16,163
You've got to marshal your strength.
Prioritize. Conserve your energy.

1554
01:32:16,535 --> 01:32:18,605
I can't put her on the stand.

1555
01:32:19,735 --> 01:32:22,329
- What choice do you have?
- I know she's lying!

1556
01:32:22,415 --> 01:32:27,091
She's lying because she didn't answer
you fast enough? She lied to you? No.

1557
01:32:27,895 --> 01:32:29,487
She said nothing.

1558
01:32:29,895 --> 01:32:31,931
Fact is, you'll never know anyway.

1559
01:32:32,175 --> 01:32:33,813
He killed those people.

1560
01:32:35,535 --> 01:32:37,127
You really believe that?

1561
01:32:38,415 --> 01:32:39,564
He set me up.

1562
01:32:39,735 --> 01:32:43,011
Cullen fucking set me up.
Melissa... the whole thing.

1563
01:32:43,375 --> 01:32:44,490
I know it.

1564
01:32:46,575 --> 01:32:48,167
Got to go with your gut.

1565
01:32:48,535 --> 01:32:49,934
That's your advice?

1566
01:32:51,375 --> 01:32:53,127
I'll back you either way.

1567
01:32:55,695 --> 01:32:57,925
Maybe it's your time to lose.

1568
01:32:59,375 --> 01:33:01,206
Think I haven't lost before?

1569
01:33:09,575 --> 01:33:12,009
We talked about this, remember?

1570
01:33:12,535 --> 01:33:13,650
Pressure.

1571
01:33:15,695 --> 01:33:17,094
Take a big whiff.

1572
01:33:19,055 --> 01:33:20,204
All rise!

1573
01:33:20,535 --> 01:33:22,605
The Honorable Armand Poe presiding.

1574
01:33:29,735 --> 01:33:31,088
Please be seated.

1575
01:33:35,495 --> 01:33:37,087
All right, Mr. Lomax...

1576
01:33:37,255 --> 01:33:39,132
...you may present your case.

1577
01:33:57,895 --> 01:33:59,044
Mr. Lomax...

1578
01:34:20,055 --> 01:34:21,886
I call Melissa Black.

1579
01:34:38,935 --> 01:34:40,448
Raise your right hand.

1580
01:34:40,575 --> 01:34:42,531
Do you swear to tell the truth,
the whole truth...

1581
01:34:42,615 --> 01:34:44,765
...nothing but the truth, so help you God?

1582
01:34:44,855 --> 01:34:45,810
I do.

1583
01:35:11,175 --> 01:35:12,927
Feeney, it's him.

1584
01:35:15,855 --> 01:35:18,688
She didn't look well.
Felix tried to talk to her.

1585
01:35:18,775 --> 01:35:21,289
- Where is she?
- Church of the Heavenly Hope.

1586
01:35:46,935 --> 01:35:47,970
Honey.

1587
01:35:49,175 --> 01:35:50,449
It's me.

1588
01:35:51,415 --> 01:35:52,609
What happened?

1589
01:35:52,855 --> 01:35:54,049
Are you okay?

1590
01:35:54,855 --> 01:35:57,528
He let himself in. You need to know that.

1591
01:35:58,135 --> 01:35:59,727
Who let himself in?

1592
01:36:00,535 --> 01:36:01,650
The bath...

1593
01:36:01,815 --> 01:36:03,726
...was running or something.

1594
01:36:04,375 --> 01:36:06,411
I didn't hear him. I swear to you.

1595
01:36:06,495 --> 01:36:08,133
And then we talked.

1596
01:36:09,095 --> 01:36:11,325
And we talked for hours.

1597
01:36:11,495 --> 01:36:13,645
And I haven't talked to anyone...

1598
01:36:13,815 --> 01:36:16,204
...really talked to anyone in so long.

1599
01:36:17,335 --> 01:36:18,848
Did somebody hurt you?

1600
01:36:19,655 --> 01:36:20,770
Yeah.

1601
01:36:21,615 --> 01:36:22,570
Who?

1602
01:36:24,935 --> 01:36:25,890
Milton.

1603
01:36:26,975 --> 01:36:29,045
What?

1604
01:36:35,295 --> 01:36:36,774
He fucked me.

1605
01:36:39,175 --> 01:36:42,770
And I think I wanted him to,
but then I just...

1606
01:36:42,935 --> 01:36:45,449
I don't know, I just couldn't stop him.

1607
01:36:46,455 --> 01:36:48,525
He just wouldn't stop.

1608
01:36:51,335 --> 01:36:52,370
When?

1609
01:36:53,495 --> 01:36:55,406
- Baby, when?
- Today.

1610
01:36:57,175 --> 01:36:58,654
The whole afternoon.

1611
01:36:58,735 --> 01:37:00,930
The whole afternoon.

1612
01:37:02,935 --> 01:37:04,209
I'm so ashamed.

1613
01:37:05,495 --> 01:37:06,484
Today?

1614
01:37:08,855 --> 01:37:09,970
Today?

1615
01:37:11,175 --> 01:37:12,733
Today he was in court.

1616
01:37:12,895 --> 01:37:15,728
He was in court in my presence
all afternoon!

1617
01:37:15,895 --> 01:37:17,089
- No!
- Yes!

1618
01:37:21,895 --> 01:37:23,214
God, no, Kevin.

1619
01:37:23,735 --> 01:37:25,566
Kevin, I'm not crazy.

1620
01:37:25,935 --> 01:37:27,573
You have to believe me.

1621
01:37:32,935 --> 01:37:34,129
Oh, Jesus.

1622
01:37:34,295 --> 01:37:36,126
He did this to me!

1623
01:37:39,575 --> 01:37:41,088
He did this to me.

1624
01:37:41,175 --> 01:37:43,086
What did you do to yourself?

1625
01:37:43,415 --> 01:37:45,007
What are we going to do?

1626
01:37:45,815 --> 01:37:47,373
What am I going to do?

1627
01:37:49,495 --> 01:37:52,931
Sign there. And your relationship.

1628
01:37:53,895 --> 01:37:57,570
She's calm now. This might be
a good time to say good night to her.

1629
01:38:05,655 --> 01:38:07,964
I know why this is happening.

1630
01:38:11,335 --> 01:38:12,973
They want you to sleep.

1631
01:38:14,695 --> 01:38:16,048
It's the money.

1632
01:38:16,975 --> 01:38:18,124
Blood money.

1633
01:38:19,015 --> 01:38:22,052
We just drank it down, both of us.

1634
01:38:22,855 --> 01:38:24,288
We knew it.

1635
01:38:25,815 --> 01:38:30,172
Winning those cases, taking the money.
We knew they were guilty.

1636
01:38:30,935 --> 01:38:33,244
But you just kept on winning...

1637
01:38:33,615 --> 01:38:34,843
...every time.

1638
01:38:40,815 --> 01:38:43,727
And I can't look at myself in the mirror.

1639
01:38:44,295 --> 01:38:46,411
And then I see a monster.

1640
01:38:49,455 --> 01:38:51,252
Don't do this, Kevin.

1641
01:38:51,495 --> 01:38:53,565
Please take me home.

1642
01:38:53,735 --> 01:38:56,124
Please don't do this.

1643
01:38:56,695 --> 01:38:58,492
I'm not crazy.

1644
01:39:13,295 --> 01:39:15,684
Doesn't Diana look fabulous?

1645
01:39:23,855 --> 01:39:26,415
Alessandra, you look ravishing.

1646
01:39:28,655 --> 01:39:29,770
Mrs. Skylar.

1647
01:39:36,175 --> 01:39:37,733
<i>We are here today...</i>

1648
01:39:38,255 --> 01:39:39,927
<i>... to remember Eddie Barzoon.</i>

1649
01:39:40,015 --> 01:39:41,368
Isn't she lovely?

1650
01:39:41,495 --> 01:39:44,851
<i>We have gathered to seek shelter</i>
<i>in our common grief.</i>

1651
01:39:45,895 --> 01:39:48,204
<i>To draw strength toward our tested faith.</i>

1652
01:39:48,295 --> 01:39:49,774
So what do they say?

1653
01:39:50,175 --> 01:39:51,528
How's Mary Ann?

1654
01:39:51,695 --> 01:39:52,969
They don't know.

1655
01:39:55,175 --> 01:39:56,608
She's falling apart.

1656
01:39:57,295 --> 01:39:58,569
Hallucinations.

1657
01:39:58,735 --> 01:39:59,804
Milton...

1658
01:40:01,735 --> 01:40:02,724
It's bad.

1659
01:40:05,735 --> 01:40:06,963
Do you have room for one more?

1660
01:40:07,055 --> 01:40:08,329
<i>Beloved father.</i>

1661
01:40:08,495 --> 01:40:09,814
<i>Devoted husband.</i>

1662
01:40:10,215 --> 01:40:11,443
<i>Trusted friend.</i>

1663
01:40:11,535 --> 01:40:13,890
<i>Esteemed colleague. Benevolent citizen.</i>

1664
01:40:14,535 --> 01:40:15,968
<i>All of these things.</i>

1665
01:40:16,815 --> 01:40:18,851
<i>And yet one thing more:</i>

1666
01:40:19,655 --> 01:40:21,293
<i>Child of God.</i>

1667
01:40:22,095 --> 01:40:25,132
<i>And it is to that Father</i>
<i>that he now returns.</i>

1668
01:40:26,095 --> 01:40:27,653
Eddie Barzoon...

1669
01:40:27,815 --> 01:40:30,534
...such a vibrant member
of our community...

1670
01:40:31,215 --> 01:40:33,285
<i>... has moved beyond us now.</i>

1671
01:40:34,095 --> 01:40:35,653
<i>He has entered...</i>

1672
01:40:36,095 --> 01:40:37,494
<i>... a new communion.</i>

1673
01:40:38,415 --> 01:40:40,724
<i>And for that it is a time of rejoicing.</i>

1674
01:40:42,255 --> 01:40:45,292
<i>God, who is our refuge and our strength.</i>

1675
01:40:46,415 --> 01:40:48,883
<i>God, who is that very present help...</i>

1676
01:40:49,295 --> 01:40:50,808
<i>... in time of trouble.</i>

1677
01:40:51,815 --> 01:40:54,090
<i>"Therefore we will not fear...</i>

1678
01:40:54,855 --> 01:40:56,732
<i>"...though the Earth should change...</i>

1679
01:40:56,815 --> 01:40:59,613
<i>"...though the mountains shake</i>
<i>in the heart of the sea...</i>

1680
01:40:59,695 --> 01:41:01,970
<i>"...though its waters roar and foam...</i>

1681
01:41:02,375 --> 01:41:05,173
<i>"...though the mountains tremble</i>
<i>with its tumult. "</i>

1682
01:41:05,415 --> 01:41:07,133
<i>We cannot fear too long...</i>

1683
01:41:07,695 --> 01:41:09,208
<i>... for Eddie Barzoon...</i>

1684
01:41:09,295 --> 01:41:10,694
<i>... has gone home.</i>

1685
01:41:29,295 --> 01:41:30,330
Mr. Lomax?

1686
01:41:30,415 --> 01:41:32,645
No comment.
I'll have something for you later.

1687
01:41:32,735 --> 01:41:34,248
I'm a friend of Eddie Barzoon.

1688
01:41:34,335 --> 01:41:36,690
You don't know me,
but Eddie mentioned your name.

1689
01:41:36,775 --> 01:41:38,606
Mitch Weaver, Justice Department?

1690
01:41:38,695 --> 01:41:39,889
Staking out the funeral?

1691
01:41:39,975 --> 01:41:41,693
Looking for you, actually.

1692
01:41:42,375 --> 01:41:44,206
I'm in a hurry. I need to talk to my wife.

1693
01:41:44,295 --> 01:41:48,493
Just wanted to ask you, off the record...
I have a few questions about Eddie.

1694
01:42:05,095 --> 01:42:07,563
Milton-Chadwick-Waters
is a little more than a law firm.

1695
01:42:07,655 --> 01:42:09,486
But I assumed you knew that.

1696
01:42:09,895 --> 01:42:12,363
Vagada Holdings?
I'm sure you've heard of it.

1697
01:42:12,455 --> 01:42:15,811
London, Kinshasa, Karachi:
Arms brokering, mostly.

1698
01:42:15,975 --> 01:42:19,684
Munzer-Dietch, in Berlin, Djakarta:
Chemical weapons and toxic waste.

1699
01:42:19,855 --> 01:42:22,927
Ivanco Limited, Moscow:
Money laundering for the eastern bloc.

1700
01:42:23,015 --> 01:42:26,849
It goes on and on and on.
Milton is into everything.

1701
01:42:37,295 --> 01:42:40,810
Barzoon was coming in, Kevin.
He was going to testify.

1702
01:42:41,135 --> 01:42:43,046
DeSoto and Dibalista, Panama.

1703
01:42:43,215 --> 01:42:46,127
That firm sets up bank accounts
for judges in South America.

1704
01:42:46,215 --> 01:42:48,524
Huge drug cases, murder, everything.

1705
01:42:48,655 --> 01:42:51,374
What the fuck do you want?
He's a lawyer!

1706
01:42:52,455 --> 01:42:54,252
Now stay off my back!

1707
01:42:58,015 --> 01:43:00,324
This is a first-time last-time offer.

1708
01:43:00,895 --> 01:43:02,487
I'm learning about you.

1709
01:43:02,655 --> 01:43:05,453
I talked to some old friends
in Florida this morning.

1710
01:43:05,535 --> 01:43:06,650
The Gettys case?

1711
01:43:06,735 --> 01:43:08,487
Eighth grade teacher?

1712
01:43:10,495 --> 01:43:12,167
They found him yesterday!

1713
01:43:13,615 --> 01:43:17,005
He had the body of a 10-year-old girl
in the trunk of his car!

1714
01:43:36,015 --> 01:43:37,926
Is he all right? Get help!

1715
01:43:59,895 --> 01:44:02,250
Marie, do you want to go to the party?

1716
01:44:02,655 --> 01:44:03,644
Come on.

1717
01:44:03,775 --> 01:44:05,049
Horace will be disappointed.

1718
01:44:05,135 --> 01:44:07,330
It's a birthday party. We can sing.

1719
01:44:07,495 --> 01:44:09,451
"...indeed, His divine power...

1720
01:44:09,615 --> 01:44:13,449
"...has granted us all things
pertaining to life and piety...

1721
01:44:13,615 --> 01:44:17,051
"...through the knowledge of Him
who has called us..."

1722
01:44:20,255 --> 01:44:21,893
What are you doing here?

1723
01:44:22,815 --> 01:44:24,487
I came this morning.

1724
01:44:25,855 --> 01:44:28,494
I kept calling the house
and getting no answer.

1725
01:44:28,815 --> 01:44:30,407
I need to talk to you.

1726
01:44:30,575 --> 01:44:33,169
We got her on the first flight up
this morning.

1727
01:44:41,615 --> 01:44:43,287
Are you all right, Kevin?

1728
01:44:49,935 --> 01:44:51,084
I don't know.

1729
01:44:54,215 --> 01:44:56,888
Would you excuse us
for a moment, please?

1730
01:44:59,535 --> 01:45:01,287
How you doing, sweetie?

1731
01:45:02,495 --> 01:45:04,804
I know something
that'll make you feel better.

1732
01:45:04,895 --> 01:45:06,169
There.

1733
01:45:09,455 --> 01:45:11,889
I shouldn't have left. I knew it.

1734
01:45:13,335 --> 01:45:15,053
I'll never forgive myself.

1735
01:45:15,815 --> 01:45:19,444
- There's nothing you could've done.
- I could've told you the truth.

1736
01:45:20,975 --> 01:45:22,044
About what?

1737
01:45:22,775 --> 01:45:25,812
Baptist Endeavor Youth Crusade, 1966.

1738
01:45:26,575 --> 01:45:28,531
I was here in New York.

1739
01:45:29,375 --> 01:45:32,253
That night in the elevator,
you never let me answer.

1740
01:45:33,735 --> 01:45:34,770
What are you talking about?

1741
01:45:34,855 --> 01:45:37,767
I stayed here a week in the Tremont Hotel.

1742
01:45:38,895 --> 01:45:42,046
They had a restaurant downstairs
where we ate almost every meal.

1743
01:45:42,135 --> 01:45:43,204
Wait. Stop.

1744
01:45:43,295 --> 01:45:45,855
Your father was a waiter in that restaurant.

1745
01:45:47,815 --> 01:45:48,850
My father?

1746
01:45:52,695 --> 01:45:54,572
This is great, Ma.

1747
01:45:57,175 --> 01:45:58,210
Honey, please listen.

1748
01:45:58,295 --> 01:45:59,171
Now?

1749
01:45:59,375 --> 01:46:00,854
You do this now?

1750
01:46:01,175 --> 01:46:03,006
Your timing, it's superb.

1751
01:46:03,095 --> 01:46:05,928
You wait 30 years,
you fly up here, you pick today?

1752
01:46:07,255 --> 01:46:11,407
Obviously I'm not under enough pressure.
I don't have enough on my mind!

1753
01:46:13,655 --> 01:46:15,134
Listen to me!

1754
01:46:20,775 --> 01:46:24,688
"Behold, I send you out as sheep
amidst the wolves!"

1755
01:46:30,455 --> 01:46:32,844
Don't you look beautiful now.

1756
01:46:36,815 --> 01:46:38,248
Take a look and see.

1757
01:46:39,015 --> 01:46:41,131
It's all right, dear. Look.

1758
01:46:41,255 --> 01:46:42,131
No.

1759
01:46:42,295 --> 01:46:44,047
Go on, take a look.

1760
01:46:44,375 --> 01:46:46,605
See how beautiful you are?

1761
01:46:53,295 --> 01:46:54,648
See?

1762
01:47:02,015 --> 01:47:03,209
What happened?

1763
01:47:03,295 --> 01:47:04,648
She attacked me.

1764
01:47:08,855 --> 01:47:10,083
Open the door.

1765
01:47:10,615 --> 01:47:12,207
Open the door, Mar.

1766
01:47:15,575 --> 01:47:17,133
Open the door!

1767
01:47:20,535 --> 01:47:21,604
It's okay.

1768
01:47:21,815 --> 01:47:23,043
Open the door!

1769
01:47:24,855 --> 01:47:26,254
Come on!

1770
01:47:26,615 --> 01:47:27,843
Open the door!

1771
01:47:31,015 --> 01:47:32,414
Open the door, Mar!

1772
01:47:32,975 --> 01:47:36,365
Oh, my God! Get somebody! Go! Go!
Mar, look at me!

1773
01:47:37,095 --> 01:47:38,608
Somebody! Help!

1774
01:47:41,135 --> 01:47:42,170
Get help!

1775
01:47:42,775 --> 01:47:44,128
Go!

1776
01:47:50,295 --> 01:47:51,364
Sweetheart!

1777
01:47:55,735 --> 01:47:56,850
Look at me!

1778
01:47:57,015 --> 01:47:58,209
I love you.

1779
01:48:07,255 --> 01:48:08,688
What have you done?

1780
01:48:08,775 --> 01:48:10,413
What have you done?

1781
01:48:12,055 --> 01:48:14,285
We need a doctor in here!

1782
01:48:14,775 --> 01:48:16,731
We need a doctor!

1783
01:48:18,575 --> 01:48:21,294
Please stay with me, Mar!

1784
01:48:22,615 --> 01:48:24,014
Stay with me, Mar!

1785
01:48:24,175 --> 01:48:26,131
Get Dr. Job in here now!

1786
01:48:26,455 --> 01:48:29,288
Sir, get away so that I can help her. Now!

1787
01:48:29,775 --> 01:48:31,413
Sir, off! Go!

1788
01:48:32,015 --> 01:48:33,414
Come on. Come on.

1789
01:48:34,455 --> 01:48:37,174
- Help her.
- Out of the way.

1790
01:48:37,735 --> 01:48:40,454
Get Dr. Job, please! I'm losing her!

1791
01:48:55,575 --> 01:48:57,008
Finish the story.

