Bliss on tap.

2059
02:02:36,775 --> 02:02:39,084
Bliss any way you want it.

2060
02:02:41,615 --> 02:02:43,651
That first line of cocaine.

2061
02:02:44,175 --> 02:02:46,769
That walk into a strange girl's bedroom.

2062
02:02:48,495 --> 02:02:49,564
Familiar?

2063
02:02:50,935 --> 02:02:53,529
You're gonna have to do
a little better than that.

2064
02:02:53,615 --> 02:02:54,764
I know.

2065
02:02:55,535 --> 02:02:57,253
I'm just getting warmed up.

2066
02:02:57,615 --> 02:03:01,130
You want more, don't you?
You deserve more.

2067
02:03:01,295 --> 02:03:03,525
How about the thing you love the most?

2068
02:03:04,015 --> 02:03:05,653
A smile from a jury.

2069
02:03:05,975 --> 02:03:09,934
That cold courtroom
just giving itself over...

2070
02:03:11,055 --> 02:03:13,125
...bending to your strength.

2071
02:03:14,575 --> 02:03:16,088
I get that on my own.

2072
02:03:16,215 --> 02:03:18,046
Not like this.

2073
02:03:18,215 --> 02:03:20,524
I take the bricks out of the briefcase.

2074
02:03:20,695 --> 02:03:22,128
I give you pleasure.

2075
02:03:23,215 --> 02:03:24,330
No strings!

2076
02:03:24,495 --> 02:03:25,814
Freedom, baby...

2077
02:03:26,135 --> 02:03:28,524
...is never having to say you're sorry.

2078
02:03:30,095 --> 02:03:31,892
This is revolution, Kevin.

2079
02:03:34,575 --> 02:03:35,690
<i>"It happened</i>

2080
02:03:36,815 --> 02:03:38,248
<i>"In Monterrey</i>

2081
02:03:39,535 --> 02:03:41,287
<i>"A long time ago"</i>

2082
02:03:42,295 --> 02:03:43,853
Forget about him.

2083
02:03:44,535 --> 02:03:45,888
This is about us.

2084
02:03:47,215 --> 02:03:49,126
<i>"In old Mexico</i>

2085
02:03:50,935 --> 02:03:54,769
<i>"Stars and steel guitars and luscious lips</i>

2086
02:03:54,855 --> 02:03:56,493
<i>"As red as wine"</i>

2087
02:03:56,655 --> 02:03:59,169
It's been so hard for me to wait for you.

2088
02:04:00,375 --> 02:04:01,649
Why the law?

2089
02:04:02,855 --> 02:04:05,733
Cut the shit, Dad! Why lawyers?
Why the law?

2090
02:04:05,815 --> 02:04:09,490
Because the law, my boy,
puts us into everything.

2091
02:04:10,455 --> 02:04:14,687
It's the ultimate backstage pass.
It's the new priesthood, baby.

2092
02:04:15,255 --> 02:04:18,053
Did you know there are more students
in law school...

2093
02:04:18,135 --> 02:04:20,126
...than lawyers walking the Earth?

2094
02:04:20,215 --> 02:04:21,648
We're coming out...

2095
02:04:22,375 --> 02:04:23,967
...guns blazing!

2096
02:04:25,255 --> 02:04:26,927
The two of you...

2097
02:04:27,095 --> 02:04:30,929
...all of us,
acquittal after acquittal after acquittal...

2098
02:04:31,015 --> 02:04:34,610
...until the stench of it reaches
so high and far into Heaven...

2099
02:04:34,775 --> 02:04:38,051
...it chokes the whole fucking lot of them!

2100
02:04:40,055 --> 02:04:42,046
In the Bible, you lose.

2101
02:04:43,335 --> 02:04:45,246
We're destined to lose, Dad.

2102
02:04:45,375 --> 02:04:47,366
Consider the source, Son!

2103
02:04:49,015 --> 02:04:50,050
Besides...

2104
02:04:50,215 --> 02:04:52,046
...we'll write our own book.

2105
02:04:52,135 --> 02:04:53,887
Chapter one.

2106
02:04:54,775 --> 02:04:56,766
Right here. This altar.

2107
02:04:57,575 --> 02:04:58,928
This moment.

2108
02:04:59,495 --> 02:05:01,008
Will you stop talking?

2109
02:05:01,095 --> 02:05:02,448
You talk too much.

2110
02:05:03,015 --> 02:05:04,289
Both of you.

2111
02:05:07,415 --> 02:05:08,530
Look at me.

2112
02:05:09,975 --> 02:05:11,328
Just look at me.

2113
02:05:20,855 --> 02:05:23,449
She is really stunning.

2114
02:05:29,415 --> 02:05:30,768
Who am I?

2115
02:05:49,975 --> 02:05:52,364
I've wanted you from the moment we met.

2116
02:06:01,575 --> 02:06:04,135
The virtue of the Devil is in his loins.

2117
02:06:07,815 --> 02:06:09,248
What about love?

2118
02:06:13,095 --> 02:06:14,164
Overrated.

2119
02:06:14,615 --> 02:06:15,525
Biochemically...

2120
02:06:15,615 --> 02:06:19,893
...no different than eating
large quantities of chocolate.

2121
02:06:21,655 --> 02:06:25,091
In two minutes you won't be thinking
about Mary Ann ever again.

2122
02:06:25,335 --> 02:06:26,529
Come here.

2123
02:06:28,055 --> 02:06:30,091
She's right, my son.

2124
02:06:36,615 --> 02:06:40,210
It's time to step up and take what's yours.

2125
02:06:44,935 --> 02:06:46,129
You're right.

2126
02:06:48,455 --> 02:06:49,808
It's time.

2127
02:06:50,375 --> 02:06:52,047
Free will, right?

2128
02:06:57,055 --> 02:06:58,170
No!

2129
02:07:11,695 --> 02:07:13,128
Damn you!

2130
02:07:16,295 --> 02:07:18,206
Enough!

2131
02:07:20,055 --> 02:07:22,523
Haven't I given enough?

2132
02:08:23,895 --> 02:08:25,328
It was a nice run.

2133
02:08:25,575 --> 02:08:27,486
Had to close out someday.

2134
02:08:28,295 --> 02:08:29,808
Nobody wins them all.

2135
02:09:17,335 --> 02:09:19,326
What are you doing, baby?

2136
02:09:21,255 --> 02:09:22,574
Are you okay?

2137
02:09:25,495 --> 02:09:27,008
I am now.

2138
02:09:30,535 --> 02:09:32,048
All rise.

2139
02:09:32,455 --> 02:09:35,367
The Honorable Judge Garson Deeds
presiding.

2140
02:09:38,215 --> 02:09:39,648
Please be seated.

2141
02:09:43,575 --> 02:09:46,135
You're still under oath, young lady.

2142
02:09:49,135 --> 02:09:50,329
Your witness.

2143
02:10:01,735 --> 02:10:03,168
Mr. Lomax?

2144
02:10:07,655 --> 02:10:08,804
Your Honor...

2145
02:10:10,535 --> 02:10:12,491
...I'm terribly sorry.

2146
02:10:13,735 --> 02:10:16,124
But I can no longer represent my client.

2147
02:10:18,575 --> 02:10:20,725
I need to be replaced as counsel.

2148
02:10:20,815 --> 02:10:22,885
Order. Order! Order!

2149
02:10:23,855 --> 02:10:25,573
I adjourn this court.

2150
02:10:25,935 --> 02:10:29,371
This is outrageous. Are you aware
of the consequences of this action?

2151
02:10:29,455 --> 02:10:30,570
I am, sir.

2152
02:10:30,735 --> 02:10:34,205
I want to see both attorneys
in my chambers immediately.

2153
02:10:34,375 --> 02:10:38,004
I'm going to adjourn this trial
until 9 a.m. Tomorrow morning.

2154
02:10:39,175 --> 02:10:40,813
I trusted you to defend me.

2155
02:10:40,895 --> 02:10:43,045
You swore you would! You'll burn for this!

2156
02:10:43,135 --> 02:10:45,729
You just made the biggest mistake
of your life!

2157
02:10:46,735 --> 02:10:48,646
Baby, what are you doing?

2158
02:10:51,855 --> 02:10:53,288
The right thing.

2159
02:10:54,055 --> 02:10:55,693
I think the right thing.

2160
02:10:59,495 --> 02:11:00,484
Here they are.

2161
02:11:00,575 --> 02:11:02,486
- Are you gonna be disbarred?
- I don't know.

2162
02:11:02,575 --> 02:11:05,214
- How's it feel to lose your first case?
- No comment.

2163
02:11:05,295 --> 02:11:09,129
Ain't it better to talk to them all at once?
Press conference tomorrow?

2164
02:11:09,295 --> 02:11:12,526
He ain't going to talk to you now.
Eight o'clock tomorrow morning.

2165
02:11:12,615 --> 02:11:13,889
That's it.

2166
02:11:14,055 --> 02:11:15,727
This is the story you dreamed about.

2167
02:11:15,815 --> 02:11:18,249
- There is no story.
- Bullshit.

2168
02:11:18,415 --> 02:11:21,691
A lawyer with a crisis of conscience?
You gotta be kidding. It's huge!

2169
02:11:21,775 --> 02:11:24,494
They're going to disbar me.
Write about that.

2170
02:11:25,455 --> 02:11:27,525
Wait a second. Can they do that?

2171
02:11:27,695 --> 02:11:29,174
Not when I get through with the story.

2172
02:11:29,255 --> 02:11:31,485
You got to give me an exclusive.

2173
02:11:31,655 --> 02:11:35,364
This is wire service. This is "60 Minutes."

2174
02:11:35,535 --> 02:11:38,845
This is a story that needs to be told.
It's you.

2175
02:11:39,175 --> 02:11:40,654
You're a star.

2176
02:11:44,335 --> 02:11:45,563
Baby.

2177
02:11:47,815 --> 02:11:49,453
Call me in the morning.

2178
02:11:50,095 --> 02:11:52,609
You got it. First thing.

2179
02:12:01,935 --> 02:12:03,209
Vanity...

2180
02:12:03,655 --> 02:12:05,805
...definitely my favorite sin.

2181
02:13:20,535 --> 02:13:23,333
Subtitles : Filou ;-)
